### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

Consider a component with the following template:

```html
<button (click)="show = true">Show</button>

@defer (when show) {
<app-chart />
}
@placeholder {
<div>Something until the loading starts</div>
}
@loading (after 500ms) {
<div>Loading...</div>
}
```

if the unit test uses the default `DeferBlockBehavior.Manual` behavior, then the following fails:

```ts
describe('AppComponent', () => {
  beforeEach(() => TestBed.configureTestingModule({}));

  it('should succeed without tick', async () => {
    const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(AppComponent);
    fixture.detectChanges();

    // placeholder is displayed first
    const placeholder = fixture.nativeElement.querySelector('div');
    expect(placeholder.textContent).toContain('Something until the loading starts');

    const deferBlocks = await fixture.getDeferBlocks();
    // only one defer block should be found
    expect(deferBlocks.length).toBe(1);

    // loading
    await deferBlocks[0].render(DeferBlockState.Loading);

    const loadingBlock = fixture.nativeElement.querySelector('div');
    expect(loadingBlock.textContent).toContain('Loading...');

    // complete
    await deferBlocks[0].render(DeferBlockState.Complete);

    const loadedBlock = fixture.nativeElement.querySelector('div');
    expect(loadedBlock.textContent).toContain('Some lazy-loaded content');
  });
});
```

You currently need to use tick in the test to make it succeed:

```ts
it('should succeed with tick', fakeAsync(async () => {
    const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(AppComponent);
    fixture.detectChanges();

    // placeholder is displayed first
    const placeholder = fixture.nativeElement.querySelector('div');
    expect(placeholder.textContent).toContain('Something until the loading starts');

    const deferBlocks = await fixture.getDeferBlocks();
    // only one defer block should be found
    expect(deferBlocks.length).toBe(1);

    // loading
    await deferBlocks[0].render(DeferBlockState.Loading);
    // should not be necessary
    tick(500);
    fixture.detectChanges();

    const loadingBlock = fixture.nativeElement.querySelector('div');
    expect(loadingBlock.textContent).toContain('Loading...');

    // complete
    await deferBlocks[0].render(DeferBlockState.Complete);

    const loadedBlock = fixture.nativeElement.querySelector('div');
    expect(loadedBlock.textContent).toContain('Some lazy-loaded content');
  }));
```

It seems weird that this is needed, and this was working in `next.7` (regression is in `next.8`)

